channel.title: Latest News and News Headlines | Daily Telegraph

item.title: Victoria records 603 new cases
item.description: Victoria has recorded 603 local cases of Covid-19 overnight, along with one death.

item.title: New charges over Eastern Freeway crash
item.description: The trucking company involved in the Eastern Freeway crash that killed four police officers has been hit with fresh charges over the tragic incident.

item.title: Global stocks sink on Evergrande contagion fears
item.description: World stocks sank Monday as trading floors were gripped by contagion fears from the expected collapse of debt-plagued Chinese property giant Evergrande, while spiking energy costs and the standoff over the US borrowing limit also put investors on red alert.

item.title: Fresh probe in boy’s fire death
item.description: Police have launched a fresh appeal for information into a house fire which killed a teenage boy.

item.title: Man tried to kidnap ‘slashed’ woman: cops
item.description: A man has been charged with the attempted robbery and kidnap of a 34-year-old woman who was attacked with a knife while taking a morning walk on the Gold Coast on Monday.

item.title: Biden administration doubles US refugee admissions
item.description: The Biden administration announced Monday that it would double the number of refugees it will accept in the coming fiscal year to 125,000, amid rising pressure from people fleeing Afghanistan and other countries.

item.title: Construction shut down after protests
item.description: The Victorian construction industry will be closed in locked down parts of the state for two weeks in response to violent protests in Melbourne.

item.title: US to end travel bans for vaccinated passengers
item.description: The United States announced Monday it will lift Covid travel bans on all air passengers in November if they are fully vaccinated and undergo testing and contact tracing.

item.title: Trudeau future on the line as Canadians vote in pandemic election
item.description: Canadians packed into long queues Monday to cast ballots in elections that are headed for a photo finish, with liberal Prime Minister Justin Trudeau's bid for a third term threatened by rookie conservative leader Erin O'Toole's strong challenge.

item.title: Major change coming to Woolies
item.description: Australia will soon welcome its first commercial recycling plant that uses enzymes to “eat” plastic and break it down into its core molecules so they can be reused.
